{
  "title": "Introduction to the Green Future Group",
  "transcript": "I'm Mark Corrigan and I'm the group leader of the Green Future Group. Our group was established in the early 2000s in Canada by a group of seven dedicated environmental researchers from Toronto. The goal of Green Future was to look at the most worrying environmental trends across Canada and consider the root causes of these problems. The first problem we came across is related to global warming, specifically to the damage to natural habitats of wildlife in the colder northern part of the country. There is definitely a major threat to wildlife from the warming climate, and large stretches of the northern mountains have seen their snow melt at a disturbing speed. What's more, there is a threat to freshwater fish as a result of rising water temperatures. A lot of people want to know about the Green Future group, and have shown enthusiasm for getting involved in our work. Membership of Green Future has been developing steadily in recent years and people are surprised at how easy it is to join us. You just need to spend five minutes filling out our online form and pay £35 for membership. Aside from protecting wildlife and natural habitats, we are also concerned about ourselves with making the area good for agriculture. Lots of people have appreciated our work, especially those involved in our volunteer programs.[cite: 6]",
